description.p:
an oil pump coaxially driven by the crankshaft, for supplying oil to respective engine sections, the oil pump including a pump housing;


wherein the pump housing is disposed between a front cover for covering the timing chain and a sprocket for the timing chain, while leaving a clearance relative to the front cover; and


wherein the pump housing is fastened to a cylinder block of the engine so as to straddle the timing chain.
